Domestic deals worth $121b sealed at China-Eurasia Expo |Economy |chinadaily.com.cn
The third China-Eurasia Expo in Urumqi, capital of the Xinjiang Uygur autonomous region, has helped to seal domestic deals worth 738.7 billion yuan ($121 billion), said Li Jingyuan, Expo secretary-general.
There was $3.73 billion in foreign trade deals at the Expo up to Friday. The Expo started on Monday and concludes on Saturday.
The biggest single domestic deal is for more than 15.6 billion yuan.
About 200,000 people have visited the exhibition which has drawn more than 1,560 companies and corporations.
